The paper deals with communication complexity, which is a central topic in theoretical computer science and falls under the category of cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also involves information theory, specifically the use of Gaussian space, which suggests a possible fit under cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also has implications for data stream algorithms, which could place it under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The geometric statement regarding correlations in Gaussian space could also suggest a connection to computational geometry, placing it under cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Finally, the paper involves the estimation of frequency moments, which is a problem in data mining and could place it under cs.DM (Data Mining).
